<headline>Wind Chill Watch issued February 01 at 3:30AM EST until February 04 at 4:00PM EST by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...WIND CHILL WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM LATE THURSDAY NIGHT
THROUGH SATURDAY AFTERNOON...
* WHAT...Dangerously cold wind chills possible. Wind chills as
low as 30 to 45 below zero.
* WHERE...The Mohawk and Schoharie Valleys, Glens Falls Saratoga
region, Capital District and northern Taconics of eastern New
York and all of southern Vermont.
* WHEN...From late Thursday night through Saturday afternoon.
* IMPACTS...The dangerously cold wind chills could cause
frostbite on exposed skin in as little as 10 minutes.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The coldest wind chills will be Friday
night into Saturday morning.</description>
<instruction>Monitor the latest forecasts for updates on this situation.</instruction>
